          "pos": "adjective",
          "definition": "sticking to or worshipping books as if they are sacred; excessively reverent toward texts.",
          "examples": [
            "The critic warned against bibliolatrous attitudes that treat every manuscript as flawless.",
            "Her bibliolatrous devotion to the novel blurred critical judgment."
